      "message": "We were tripping up on it when running on the vkddl bot. This function and contains() already struggle with numerical precision (see the kScale comment above). I found that if I adjusted kScale to 1e-2, the vkddl bot never hit the assert.\n\nEvery time I\u0027ve inspected the assertion failures, it\u0027s always been that the corner ellipse distance check is over by a very small fraction, so it hasn\u0027t indicated a bug in the code. I removed the assert entirely instead of tweaking scale because I imagined this would just lead to pointless fuzzer bugs in the future, when it doesn\u0027t really change the visual result of a clipping operation.",
